The 2017 Tony Awards have finally arrived.One year after &ldquo;Hamilton: An American Musical&rdquo; vied for a record&nbsp;16 statues&nbsp;at the annual ceremony, the Broadway scene looks a little different. Without a clear Tonys frontrunner, a number of critically-acclaimed musicals and plays competed for recognition, including favorites like the Ben Platt&ndash;led musical &ldquo;Dear Evan Hansen&rdquo; and the Pulitzer-winning play &ldquo;Sweat.&rdquo; (The former prevailed, while the latter lost to &ldquo;Oslo.&rdquo;)&nbsp;Hosted by your favorite &ldquo;House of Cards&rdquo; villain Kevin Spacey, the 71st edition of the awards show featured an impressive roster of celebrities: Mark Hamill introduced the night&rsquo;s &ldquo;In Memoriam&rdquo; segment that paid tribute to his former co-star, Carrie Fisher. Another &ldquo;Star Wars&rdquo; alum, 86-year-old James Earl Jones, was honored with a&nbsp;Tony for lifetime achievement. Bette Midler won her first competitive Tony award for her performance in &ldquo;Hello, Dolly!&rdquo; (She unfortunately did not perform; co-star David Hyde Pierce took her place.)Other stars who made appearances included Stephen Colbert, Lin-Manuel Miranda, Tina Fey, Keegan-Michael Key and more. And Broadway fans outside of New York City caught performances from several musicals beyond &ldquo;Dear Evan Hansen,&rdquo; like &ldquo;Come From Away,&rdquo; &ldquo;Groundhog Day,&rdquo; &ldquo;Natasha, Pierre &amp; The Great Comet of 1812,&rdquo; &ldquo;Falsettos&rdquo; and &ldquo;Miss Saigon.&rdquo;Taking place a year after the devastating shooting at Pulse nightclub in Orlando, Florida, the 2017 ceremony was a joyous occasion filled with emotional speeches.&nbsp;Check out every win of the night below, so you can continue the Tony toasting long after the broadcast on CBS.To analyze the upsets and snubs, check out a full list of the nominations here.Winners are underlined .&nbsp;Best Play:&ldquo;Sweat&rdquo; &rdquo;Indecent&rdquo; &rdquo;A Doll&rsquo;s House, Part 2&rdquo; &rdquo;Oslo&rdquo; Best Musical:&ldquo;Dear Evan Hansen&rdquo;&nbsp; &ldquo;Natasha, Pierre &amp;&nbsp;The Great Comet of 1812&rdquo; &ldquo;Come From Away&rdquo;&nbsp; &ldquo;Groundhog Day&rdquo;Best Revival of a Play:&ldquo;Jitney&rdquo;&nbsp; &ldquo;Six Degrees of Separation&rdquo; &ldquo;The Little Foxes&rdquo;&nbsp; &ldquo;Present Laughter&rdquo;Best Revival of a Musical:&ldquo;Hello, Dolly!&rdquo; &nbsp; &ldquo;Falsettos&rdquo;&nbsp; &ldquo;Miss Saigon&rdquo;&nbsp;&nbsp;Best Actor in a Play:Denis Arndt, &ldquo;Heisenberg&rdquo;&nbsp;&nbsp; Chris Cooper, &ldquo;A Doll&rsquo;s House Part 2&rdquo; Cory Hawkins, &ldquo;Six Degrees of Separation&rdquo; Kevin Kline, &ldquo;Present Laughter&rdquo; Jefferson Mays, &ldquo;Oslo&rdquo;&nbsp;Best Actress in a Play:Cate Blanchett, &ldquo;The Present&rdquo;&nbsp; Jennifer Ehle, &ldquo;Oslo&rdquo; Sally Field, &ldquo;The Glass Menagerie&rdquo;&nbsp;&nbsp; Laura Linney, &ldquo;The Little Foxes&rdquo; Laurie Metcalf, &ldquo;A Doll&rsquo;s House Part 2&rdquo; Best Actor in a Musical:Christian Borle, &ldquo;Falsettos&rdquo;&nbsp;&nbsp; Josh Groban, &ldquo;Natasha, Pierre &amp;&nbsp;The Great Comet of 1812&rdquo; David Hyde Pierce, &ldquo;Hello, Dolly!&rdquo; Andy Karl, &ldquo;Groundhog Day&rdquo;&nbsp; Ben Platt, &ldquo;Dear Evan Hansen&rdquo;&nbsp; Best Actress in a Musical:&nbsp;Christine Ebersole, &ldquo;War Paint&rdquo; Denee Benton, &ldquo;Natasha, Pierre &amp;&nbsp;The Great Comet of 1812&rdquo;&nbsp; Patti LuPone, &ldquo;War Paint&rdquo;&nbsp; Bette Midler, &ldquo;Hello, Dolly!&rdquo; Eva Noblezada, &ldquo;Miss Saigon&rdquo;Best Direction of a Play:Sam Gold, &ldquo;A Doll&rsquo;s House, Part 2&rdquo; Ruben Santiago-Hudson, &ldquo;Jitney&rdquo; Bartlett Sher, &ldquo;Oslo&rdquo; Daniel Sullivan, &ldquo;Lillian Hellman&rsquo;s The Little Foxes&rdquo; Rebecca Taichman, &ldquo;Indecent&rdquo; Best Direction of a Musical:Christopher Ashley, &ldquo;Come From Away&rdquo; Rachel Chavkin, &ldquo;Natasha, Pierre &amp; The Great Comet of 1812&rdquo; Michael Greif, &ldquo;Dear Evan Hansen&rdquo; Matthew Warchus, &ldquo;Groundhog Day&rdquo; Jerry Zaks, &ldquo;Hello, Dolly!&rdquo;Best Book of a Musical:&ldquo;Come From Away,&rdquo; Irene Sankoff and David Hein &ldquo;Dear Evan Hansen,&rdquo; Steven Levenson &rdquo;Groundhog Day,&rdquo;&nbsp;Danny Rubin &rdquo;Natasha, Pierre &amp; The Great Comet of 1812,&rdquo; Dave MalloyBest Original Score:&ldquo;Come From Away,&rdquo; Irene Sankoff and David Hein &rdquo;Dear Evan Hansen,&rdquo; Benj Pasek &amp; Justin Paul &rdquo;Groundhog Day,&rdquo; Tim Minchin &rdquo;Natasha, Pierre &amp; The Great Comet of 1812,&rdquo; Dave MalloyBest Featured Actor in a Play:&nbsp;Michael Aronov, &ldquo;Oslo&rdquo; Danny DeVito, &ldquo;The Price&rdquo; Nathan Lane, &ldquo;The Front Page&rdquo; Richard Thomas, &ldquo;The Little Foxes&rdquo; John Douglas Thompson, &ldquo;Jitney&rdquo;&nbsp;Best Featured Actress in a Play:Johanna Day, &ldquo;Sweat&rdquo; Jayne Houdyshell, &ldquo;A Doll&rsquo;s House, Part 2&rdquo; Cynthia Nixon, &ldquo;The Little Foxes&rdquo; Condola Rashad, &ldquo;A Doll&rsquo;s House, Part 2&rdquo; Michelle Wilson, &ldquo;Sweat&rdquo;Best Featured Actor in a Musical:Gavin Creel, &ldquo;Hello, Dolly!&rdquo; Mike Faist, &ldquo;Dear Evan Hansen&rdquo; Andrew Rannells, &ldquo;Falsettos&rdquo; Lucas Steele, &ldquo;Natasha, Pierre &amp; The Great Comet of 1812&rdquo; Brandon Uranowitz, &ldquo;Falsettos&rdquo;Best Featured Actress in a Musical:Kate Baldwin, &ldquo;Hello, Dolly!&rdquo; Stephanie J. Block, &ldquo;Falsettos&rdquo; Jenn Colella, &ldquo;Come From Away&rdquo; Rachel Bay Jones, &ldquo;Dear Evan Hansen&rdquo; Mary Beth Peil, &ldquo;Anastasia&rdquo;&nbsp;Best Scenic Design of a Play:&nbsp;David Gallo, &ldquo;Jitney&rdquo; Nigel Hook, &ldquo;The Play That Goes Wrong&rdquo; Douglas W. Schmidt, &ldquo;The Front Page&rdquo; Michael Yeargan, &ldquo;Oslo&rdquo;&nbsp;Best Scenic Design of a Musical:&nbsp;Rob Howell, &ldquo;Groundhog 